    "content": "2025.04.02 @ 21:26:00 IST\nVenture + Political Manifesto ${toc}\nManifesto of the Oppressed: A Call for Socialist Revolution Comrades, workers, tillers of the soil, the exploited of all stripes!\nFor too long, we have suffered under the crushing weight of a rigged system. The capitalist machine grinds on, churning out profit for the privileged few while leaving the vast majority to toil for scraps. We are the bakers with empty cupboards, the builders sleeping in the streets, the minds overflowing with potential chained to dead-end jobs.\nThe Lies Weâ€™ve Been Sold\nThey tell us competition breeds innovation, but all it breeds is inequality. The rich hoard resources, leaving others to fight over crumbs. They preach meritocracy, while the children of privilege inherit wealth and opportunity. They claim democracy serves the people, yet our voices are drowned out by the clinking of coins in the pockets of the powerful.\nA World Transformed\nWe envision a world reborn, a world where:\nThe means of production - factories, farms, resources - are owned and controlled democratically by the people, not by a select elite. Labor is valued, not just for its profit potential, but for its contribution to society. Everyone who works deserves a fair share of the wealth they help create. Basic needs are met - food, shelter, healthcare, education - as fundamental rights, not privileges reserved for the lucky few. Power resides with the people through genuine participatory democracy, where every voice is heard and every vote counts. The Road to Revolution\nThis transformation wonâ€™t be granted by those who benefit from the current system. It will require a revolution, a collective uprising of the oppressed. We must:\nOrganize - workers, students, farmers, the marginalized - into a united front. Solidarity is our strength. Educate ourselves and others about the exploitative nature of capitalism and the possibilities of a socialist future. Take action - through strikes, protests, and civil disobedience, we will make our voices heard and disrupt the status quo. Embrace diversity - our revolution must encompass all forms of oppression, dismantling racism, sexism, and other hierarchies alongside capitalism. The Choice is Ours\nThe path ahead will not be easy. There will be challenges, setbacks, and sacrifices. But the alternative - a life of perpetual subservience - is far worse. We have the power to create a better future, a future where everyone has the opportunity to thrive.\nJoin us, comrades! Let the flames of revolution ignite! Let us build a world where freedom, equality, and solidarity are not mere slogans, but the very foundation of our society!\nA luta continua (The struggle continues!)",
